.TH "param_get_vmidfilter" 9 "param_get_vmidfilter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
param_get_vmidfilter \- Get z/VM user ID filter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" param_get_vmidfilter
.BI "(char *buffer "  ","
.BI "const struct kernel_param *kp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
Buffer to store z/VM user ID filter,
(buffer size assumption PAGE_SIZE)
.IP "kp" 12
Kernel parameter pointing to the hvc_iucv_filter array
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function stores the filter as a comma-separated list of z/VM user IDs
in \fIbuffer\fP. Typically, sysfs routines call this function for attr show.
